	<Title>
		Do you need to warm up before you exercise?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Warming up gradually revs up your cardiovascular system, increases blood flow to your muscles and raises your body temperature. Choose a warm-up activity that uses the same muscles you&apos;ll use during your workout. If you&apos;re going to run, walk briskly for five to 10 minutes. A warm-up may cause mild sweating, but it shouldn&apos;t leave you fatigued.&lt;/p&gt;
